WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.701 --> 00:00:03.100
<i>Previously on</i> Elementary...

2
00:00:03.888 --> 00:00:06.355
Hannah.
the guy laid hands on you.

3
00:00:06.357 --> 00:00:09.492
I am not nine years old
anymore. Dad.

4
00:00:09.494 --> 00:00:11.427
I want to be promoted
just as bad as the next cop.

5
00:00:11.429 --> 00:00:13.395
and I'm not just talking
about Detective.

6
00:00:13.397 --> 00:00:16.031
I want to be Captain someday.
like you.

7
00:00:17.502 --> 00:00:19.735
But it's never gonna happen
if people look at me

8
00:00:19.737 --> 00:00:21.437
and they see “victim.”

9
00:00:23.908 --> 00:00:26.242
Watson. you still over there?

10
00:00:26.244 --> 00:00:27.643
Yes. I'm still here.

11
00:00:27.645 --> 00:00:29.411
because I can't go home.
because of you.

12
00:00:29.413 --> 00:00:31.113
Why did you bring the bees
in the house anyway?

13
00:00:31.115 --> 00:00:33.716
Varroa mites are a pernicious
threat to the colony.

14
00:00:33.718 --> 00:00:35.417
I intended
a thorough inspection.

15
00:00:35.419 --> 00:00:37.186
as well as an application
of baker's sugar

16
00:00:37.188 --> 00:00:38.721
as a preventative measure.

17
00:00:38.723 --> 00:00:40.756
My thoughts were concerned
with colony collapse.

18
00:00:40.758 --> 00:00:42.491
I failed to see
the more urgent threat

19
00:00:42.493 --> 00:00:43.926
of table collapse.

20
00:00:43.928 --> 00:00:45.327
Wait a second.

21
00:00:45.329 --> 00:00:47.463
You're not talking
about my table. are you?

22
00:00:47.465 --> 00:00:49.365
The one that I bought
for my apartment?

23
00:00:49.367 --> 00:00:51.600
Two hours should be sufficient
to return the hive to stasis.

24
00:00:51.602 --> 00:00:53.102
I'll be in touch.

25
00:00:53.104 --> 00:00:55.104
Do you have a roommate?

26
00:00:55.106 --> 00:00:57.072
Nah. Don't get one.
Ever.

27
00:00:57.074 --> 00:00:58.941
Trouble in paradise?

28
00:00:58.943 --> 00:01:01.143
Well. nothing a good
exterminator couldn't solve.

29
00:01:01.145 --> 00:01:02.645
Tonight still
a good night to talk?

30
00:01:02.647 --> 00:01:04.079
Yeah. let's just
get out of here.

31
00:01:04.081 --> 00:01:06.849
I need coffee that
wasn't made by a cop.

32
00:01:08.085 --> 00:01:09.785
Three neighborhood
drugstores.

33
00:01:09.787 --> 00:01:10.953
all in my precinct.

34
00:01:10.955 --> 00:01:13.489
all robbed in
the last month.

35
00:01:15.459 --> 00:01:17.026
None of the stores
had security cameras

36
00:01:17.028 --> 00:01:18.861
but all the robberies
took place

37
00:01:18.863 --> 00:01:20.396
right when the owners were
closing up for the night.

38
00:01:20.398 --> 00:01:22.932
Descriptions of the perps
match in all three.

39
00:01:22.934 --> 00:01:24.733
and also. they only took
prescription pills.

40
00:01:24.735 --> 00:01:27.903
High street value.
Oxy. hydrocodone.

41
00:01:27.905 --> 00:01:30.072
Sounds like it was all done
by the same crew.

42
00:01:31.242 --> 00:01:33.242
I've been re-interviewing
witnesses.

43
00:01:33.244 --> 00:01:34.944
putting in extra hours.

44
00:01:34.946 --> 00:01:36.846
keeping an eye
on the other stores.

45
00:01:36.848 --> 00:01:39.348
But. uh...
I'm not making much headway.

46
00:01:39.350 --> 00:01:42.852
Is there a detective
on this case?

47
00:01:42.854 --> 00:01:44.854
Hanford.

48
00:01:46.257 --> 00:01:49.458
I'm not trying
to step on his toes. I'm...

49
00:01:49.460 --> 00:01:51.293
I don't want to be
disrespectful. but...

50
00:01:53.197 --> 00:01:55.898
...but his plate's
kind of full right now.

51
00:01:57.635 --> 00:01:58.968
It's my neighborhood.

52
00:01:58.970 --> 00:02:00.169
My partner and I. we...

53
00:02:00.171 --> 00:02:01.470
we have to look these people

54
00:02:01.472 --> 00:02:03.405
in the eye every day.

55
00:02:03.407 --> 00:02:04.807
They're scared.

56
00:02:04.809 --> 00:02:07.276
It would.
it would mean a lot to them--

57
00:02:07.278 --> 00:02:10.045
a lot to me--
if I could bring this one home.

58
00:02:11.716 --> 00:02:12.982
All right.

59
00:02:12.984 --> 00:02:14.483
I'll take a look.

60
00:02:14.485 --> 00:02:16.752
Um. I'll let you know
if anything comes up.

61
00:02:21.125 --> 00:02:23.125
<i>I know it's late here.</i>

62
00:02:23.127 --> 00:02:26.562
Uh. well. you wanted
to go to school out west. no?

63
00:02:26.564 --> 00:02:29.565
Or is it just that
I'm keeping you from a party?

64
00:02:36.841 --> 00:02:38.140
Hey. I'm-I'm sorry.

65
00:02:38.142 --> 00:02:39.808
Yeah. some drunk
and he almost hit me.

66
00:02:39.810 --> 00:02:41.277
No. no. no. no.
I'm fine. I'm fine.

67
00:02:41.279 --> 00:02:43.112
I guess the bars
must be letting out.

68
00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:51.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

69
00:02:56.227 --> 00:02:57.826
What the hell?

70
00:03:01.499 --> 00:03:03.899
Hey!

71
00:03:05.102 --> 00:03:06.769
Hey!

72
00:03:08.673 --> 00:03:09.939
Hey. man. what's wrong?

73
00:03:09.941 --> 00:03:11.407
Let's go.

74
00:03:36.867 --> 00:03:39.101
What a drunk idiot.

75
00:03:39.103 --> 00:03:41.170
I tell you. man...

76
00:03:41.172 --> 00:03:43.305
you had an angel
looking out for you tonight.

77
00:03:45.516 --> 00:03:49.516
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Elementary 3x20 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>A Stitch in Time</font>
Original Air Date on April 16. 2015

78
00:03:49.540 --> 00:03:56.040
== sync. corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

79
00:03:56.064 --> 00:04:20.424
 ♪  ♪

80
00:04:24.255 --> 00:04:25.988
You said
you knew this guy.

81
00:04:25.990 --> 00:04:27.256
I was an admirer.

82
00:04:27.258 --> 00:04:29.692
Garrison Boyd
was president

83
00:04:29.694 --> 00:04:31.493
of the Five Boroughs
Skeptics Association.

84
00:04:31.495 --> 00:04:34.430
He was a debunker
of the highest order.

85
00:04:34.432 --> 00:04:36.298
He was a bright
light of reason

86
00:04:36.300 --> 00:04:38.634
in a sea of gullibility
and magical thought.

87
00:04:39.670 --> 00:04:42.004
He was a professional doubter.

88
00:04:42.006 --> 00:04:43.272
Of...?

89
00:04:43.274 --> 00:04:45.207
Pseudoscience.
the paranormal.

90
00:04:45.209 --> 00:04:48.510
organized religion--
all the usual bollocks.

91
00:04:48.512 --> 00:04:50.379
He wrote a blog that
I rather enjoyed.

92
00:04:50.381 --> 00:04:52.014
Did he believe in crowbars?

93
00:04:52.016 --> 00:04:54.116
'Cause I'm pretty sure

94
00:04:54.118 --> 00:04:56.085
that's what caved
his skull in.

95
00:05:02.126 --> 00:05:04.593
You put the time of death
at approximately one hour

96
00:05:04.595 --> 00:05:06.128
before his car was found.

97
00:05:06.130 --> 00:05:07.930
I'm guessing whoever killed him

98
00:05:07.932 --> 00:05:09.531
was hoping that
the impact of the train

99
00:05:09.533 --> 00:05:11.133
would hide the real
cause of death.

100
00:05:12.503 --> 00:05:14.370
It says here
you removed

101
00:05:14.372 --> 00:05:16.872
a small. conical object from
beneath his right eye socket.

102
00:05:16.874 --> 00:05:19.808
After he was struck.
he fell forward.

103
00:05:19.810 --> 00:05:22.811
This got wedged
under his eye

104
00:05:22.813 --> 00:05:24.213
on the way down.

105
00:05:24.215 --> 00:05:26.148
Don't know
what it is. yet.

106
00:05:26.150 --> 00:05:28.450
but I'm sending it to the lab.
It's the tip of a hat.

107
00:05:29.787 --> 00:05:31.787
You are familiar
with the vile practice

108
00:05:31.789 --> 00:05:33.355
of lawn ornamentation?

109
00:05:33.357 --> 00:05:35.124
The worst offenders
employ garden gnomes.

110
00:05:35.126 --> 00:05:36.458
yea big. white beards...

111
00:05:36.460 --> 00:05:38.527
Pointy red hats.
If he wasn't so dead.

112
00:05:38.529 --> 00:05:40.963
I suspect Mr. Boyd
would find it ironic

113
00:05:40.965 --> 00:05:42.531
that a diminutive wood spirit

114
00:05:42.533 --> 00:05:44.667
played a role in his murder.

115
00:05:46.937 --> 00:05:49.338
He was particularly aggressive
in his pursuit of those

116
00:05:49.340 --> 00:05:52.675
who sought to profit
from their hoaxes.

117
00:05:52.677 --> 00:05:55.411
so... perhaps his persistence

118
00:05:55.413 --> 00:05:57.379
is the reason
he now lies here.

119
00:05:57.381 --> 00:05:59.415
You really think being debunked
is a reason to kill somebody?

120
00:05:59.417 --> 00:06:02.217
Some of the most aggressive
correspondence on his Web site

121
00:06:02.219 --> 00:06:04.520
came from local
ghost tour operators.

122
00:06:04.522 --> 00:06:06.422
hawkers of phony
medical cures...

123
00:06:06.424 --> 00:06:08.624
I think one recent
exposé target

124
00:06:08.626 --> 00:06:12.027
might have not so much
a reasonable motive for murder

125
00:06:12.029 --> 00:06:14.430
as a lower standard
for committing one.

126
00:06:14.432 --> 00:06:17.333
'Cause he's almost
certainly insane.

127
00:06:21.105 --> 00:06:22.771
I won't pretend
that Mr. Boyd and I

128
00:06:22.773 --> 00:06:24.940
didn't have
a contentious relationship.

129
00:06:24.942 --> 00:06:27.910
He took issue with the church
on more than one occasion.

130
00:06:27.912 --> 00:06:30.179
You mean. he took
issue with your cult.

131
00:06:31.482 --> 00:06:34.083
He misused that
term. as well.

132
00:06:34.085 --> 00:06:36.385
That's just the kind of rigid.
closed-minded thinking

133
00:06:36.387 --> 00:06:37.886
that I preach against here.

134
00:06:37.888 --> 00:06:39.355
At one time or another.

135
00:06:39.357 --> 00:06:41.256
every great religion
has been attacked

136
00:06:41.258 --> 00:06:42.725
as a cult.
Mm.

137
00:06:42.727 --> 00:06:44.159
So have most cults.

138
00:06:48.132 --> 00:06:49.898
Excuse me for a minute.
would you?

139
00:06:49.900 --> 00:06:51.333
Where are you...?

140
00:06:51.335 --> 00:06:53.736
Look. the victim published
almost two dozen

141
00:06:53.738 --> 00:06:55.738
threatening responses
you sent him.

142
00:06:55.740 --> 00:06:57.272
after he posted a few articles

143
00:06:57.274 --> 00:06:59.575
criticizing the church's
recruitment methods.

144
00:06:59.577 --> 00:07:01.643
Well. I have
the right to respond.

145
00:07:01.645 --> 00:07:03.846
if somebody publishes lies about
what we're trying to do here.

146
00:07:03.848 --> 00:07:06.148
You told Mr. Boyd
that his attacks had

147
00:07:06.150 --> 00:07:08.283
begun a chain reaction
that would lead to

148
00:07:08.285 --> 00:07:11.320
“his removal
from this physical reality.”

149
00:07:11.322 --> 00:07:13.188
We meditate here.

150
00:07:13.190 --> 00:07:15.391
We practice energy transference.

151
00:07:15.393 --> 00:07:17.259
So when I wrote to him.
I was merely

152
00:07:17.261 --> 00:07:19.228
absorbing his hateful energy

153
00:07:19.230 --> 00:07:20.929
and reflecting it back.

154
00:07:20.931 --> 00:07:23.098
Did I harm him
physically? No.

155
00:07:23.100 --> 00:07:25.000
Did I appeal
to the Quantum Source

156
00:07:25.002 --> 00:07:27.035
for swift and final justice?
Perhaps.

157
00:07:27.037 --> 00:07:29.405
In other words. you prayed
for the guy to die.

158
00:07:29.407 --> 00:07:31.774
That's not a crime.
is it?

159
00:07:31.776 --> 00:07:33.475
So we're done here.

160
00:07:33.477 --> 00:07:35.778
The church held a 12-hour
service last night.

161
00:07:35.780 --> 00:07:37.346
Attendance
was mandatory.

162
00:07:37.348 --> 00:07:40.349
so no one here could have
killed Garrison Boyd.

163
00:07:40.351 --> 00:07:42.017
We're just taking
your new friend's word for it?

164
00:07:42.019 --> 00:07:43.886
Her name is Aria.
And yes. we are.

165
00:07:43.888 --> 00:07:45.220
When it became clear
that this one

166
00:07:45.222 --> 00:07:46.622
would do little more
than proselytize.

167
00:07:46.624 --> 00:07:49.491
I scanned his herd
and realized that Aria

168
00:07:49.493 --> 00:07:50.959
was having second thoughts
about being here.

169
00:07:50.961 --> 00:07:52.828
Aria's a Level Three Conduit.

170
00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:54.530
After a brief
conversation with Aria.

171
00:07:54.532 --> 00:07:56.765
AKA Elizabeth Weinberg.

172
00:07:56.767 --> 00:07:58.534
I was able to determine

173
00:07:58.536 --> 00:08:00.169
that some unresolved
issues from her childhood

174
00:08:00.171 --> 00:08:02.704
had led to a transference
of a need for structure

175
00:08:02.706 --> 00:08:04.440
and discipline
onto Mr. Finn.

176
00:08:04.442 --> 00:08:05.674
Elizabeth agreed. and
has forthwith terminated

177
00:08:05.676 --> 00:08:06.842
her relationship
with your church.

178
00:08:06.844 --> 00:08:08.143
- What?
- So wait a second.

179
00:08:08.145 --> 00:08:09.912
Are you saying
you deprogrammed her?

180
00:08:09.914 --> 00:08:12.181
I would never use such a
rigid and closed-minded term.

181
00:08:12.183 --> 00:08:14.082
She did. however. share
some useful information

182
00:08:14.084 --> 00:08:15.250
on the church's methods.

183
00:08:15.252 --> 00:08:17.219
Apparently. their
esteemed leader

184
00:08:17.221 --> 00:08:19.521
likes to send
his acolytes out

185
00:08:19.523 --> 00:08:21.590
to follow. photograph
and harass people

186
00:08:21.592 --> 00:08:23.192
who dare to criticize him.

187
00:08:23.194 --> 00:08:25.127
So she's currently
in your office.

188
00:08:25.129 --> 00:08:27.429
e-mailing me the dossier
you compiled on Garrison Boyd.

189
00:08:27.431 --> 00:08:29.231
I'm hopeful it will. uh.
shed some additional light

190
00:08:29.233 --> 00:08:31.533
on his final days.

191
00:08:31.535 --> 00:08:33.335
Ms. Weinberg is
leaving with us.

192
00:08:33.337 --> 00:08:36.371
Any attempt to hinder her
return to her former life

193
00:08:36.373 --> 00:08:39.374
will be met with an energy
transference most unpleasant.

194
00:08:42.847 --> 00:08:44.112
Joan.

195
00:08:44.114 --> 00:08:45.414
Oh. hey.

196
00:08:45.416 --> 00:08:46.882
Heard you were helping
Hannah with something.

197
00:08:46.884 --> 00:08:48.817
Yeah. there's been
some robberies

198
00:08:48.819 --> 00:08:50.285
in her precinct.

199
00:08:50.287 --> 00:08:51.787
She wants to help.

200
00:08:51.789 --> 00:08:53.155
You sure
it's not a bother?

201
00:08:53.157 --> 00:08:54.389
No. not at all.

202
00:08:54.391 --> 00:08:55.824
I got into it
this morning

203
00:08:55.826 --> 00:08:57.226
and now I'm
helping Sherlock

204
00:08:57.228 --> 00:08:58.660
with this homicide
he's working.

205
00:08:58.662 --> 00:08:59.962
Hmm.

206
00:08:59.964 --> 00:09:01.163
Just make sure she knows

207
00:09:01.165 --> 00:09:03.031
whose consultant
you really are.

208
00:09:03.033 --> 00:09:05.033
All right.

209
00:09:13.611 --> 00:09:15.677
So when were you
going to inform me

210
00:09:15.679 --> 00:09:17.613
that we're assisting
Hannah Gregson on a case?

211
00:09:17.615 --> 00:09:19.615
You could hear
all that?

212
00:09:19.617 --> 00:09:21.884
<i>We</i> aren't helping her. okay?

213
00:09:21.886 --> 00:09:23.151
I am.

214
00:09:23.153 --> 00:09:24.920
And it's not a secret.

215
00:09:24.922 --> 00:09:26.388
I'm just gonna run down
a lead or two.

216
00:09:26.390 --> 00:09:27.623
It shouldn't take too much time.

217
00:09:27.625 --> 00:09:29.024
It took time this morning.

218
00:09:29.026 --> 00:09:31.159
So is this everything
from the church?

219
00:09:31.161 --> 00:09:33.762
It is a testament to the
insidiousness of cult thinking:

220
00:09:33.764 --> 00:09:36.732
A charismatic loon like Finn
warps impressionable minds

221
00:09:36.734 --> 00:09:39.902
and then sends them
to stalk and harass.

222
00:09:39.904 --> 00:09:42.638
And here I thought they just
sold flowers at the airport.

223
00:09:42.640 --> 00:09:44.306
I find the practice repulsive.

224
00:09:44.308 --> 00:09:46.575
but in this case. it may have
played in our favor.

225
00:09:46.577 --> 00:09:48.343
Two cult members
were assigned

226
00:09:48.345 --> 00:09:50.746
to Garrison Boyd
in the weeks before his murder.

227
00:09:50.748 --> 00:09:53.715
Thanks to their long lenses
and meticulous

228
00:09:53.717 --> 00:09:55.617
note-taking.
we may have

229
00:09:55.619 --> 00:09:57.452
a person of interest...

230
00:09:57.454 --> 00:10:00.522
a man by the name
of Collin Eisely.

231
00:10:02.359 --> 00:10:03.725
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

232
00:10:03.727 --> 00:10:05.761
I need to catch up
a little. here.

233
00:10:05.763 --> 00:10:07.663
Have I been under
police surveillance?

234
00:10:07.665 --> 00:10:10.432
No. those were taken by someone
who was interested in that man.

235
00:10:10.434 --> 00:10:11.867
Garrison Boyd.

236
00:10:11.869 --> 00:10:13.669
We have hundreds
of photographs of him.

237
00:10:13.671 --> 00:10:15.270
in all manner
of activities.

238
00:10:15.272 --> 00:10:17.039
Those. however.
are the only ones

239
00:10:17.041 --> 00:10:19.207
where he appears to be in heated
altercation with a man

240
00:10:19.209 --> 00:10:21.510
two days before he was murdered.

241
00:10:21.512 --> 00:10:22.578
This guy was murdered?

242
00:10:22.580 --> 00:10:23.946
Last night.

243
00:10:23.948 --> 00:10:25.747
Do you want to tell us
how you knew him?

244
00:10:25.749 --> 00:10:27.215
I didn't.

245
00:10:27.217 --> 00:10:29.117
Uh... the day these were taken.

246
00:10:29.119 --> 00:10:30.719
he was waiting for me
outside my building.

247
00:10:30.721 --> 00:10:32.621
I'd never seen him before.

248
00:10:34.024 --> 00:10:35.991
I'm confused.

249
00:10:35.993 --> 00:10:38.994
Does being accosted by a lunatic
make me a murder suspect?

250
00:10:38.996 --> 00:10:40.929
Well. that depends on
why he accosted you.

251
00:10:42.600 --> 00:10:44.466
I'm in real estate.

252
00:10:44.468 --> 00:10:46.001
Late last year. I looked

253
00:10:46.003 --> 00:10:47.970
at some beach properties
out on Long Island.

254
00:10:47.972 --> 00:10:50.238
I made this woman an offer
on her house. she said no.

255
00:10:50.240 --> 00:10:52.174
A few months later.

256
00:10:52.176 --> 00:10:54.543
this nut comes
out of the woodwork

257
00:10:54.545 --> 00:10:57.613
and accuses me of trying
to scare her into moving.

258
00:10:57.615 --> 00:10:59.114
Scare her how?

259
00:10:59.116 --> 00:11:00.482
According to him.

260
00:11:00.484 --> 00:11:02.484
she was hearing things
in her house.

261
00:11:02.486 --> 00:11:05.373
Voices. banging.
I don't know.

262
00:11:05.374 --> 00:11:07.793
She thought it was ghosts.
he thought it was me.

263
00:11:07.817 --> 00:11:08.357
Was it?

264
00:11:08.359 --> 00:11:10.025
Of course not.

265
00:11:10.027 --> 00:11:12.594
She didn't want to sell.
I moved on-- end of story.

266
00:11:12.596 --> 00:11:13.996
Ah.

267
00:11:13.998 --> 00:11:15.764
I see you've
amassed. um.

268
00:11:15.766 --> 00:11:17.766
quite an art collection
here. Mr. Eisely.

269
00:11:17.768 --> 00:11:20.202
That's an interest that
requires a great deal of money

270
00:11:20.204 --> 00:11:22.004
and a very
competitive spirit.

271
00:11:22.006 --> 00:11:23.538
I imagine you're not
the sort of person

272
00:11:23.540 --> 00:11:25.340
who takes “no”
for an answer very often.

273
00:11:25.342 --> 00:11:26.775
I'm also not the sort

274
00:11:26.777 --> 00:11:28.143
who goes around scaring
little old ladies.

275
00:11:28.145 --> 00:11:30.112
Can you tell us
where you were last night

276
00:11:30.114 --> 00:11:32.514
between the hours
of 10:00 p.m. and midnight?

277
00:11:32.516 --> 00:11:34.516
At a retirement party
for a friend.

278
00:11:34.518 --> 00:11:37.285
A few of us went out
for drinks after that.

279
00:11:38.589 --> 00:11:41.390
I'll get you
their names and numbers.

280
00:11:47.131 --> 00:11:49.498
If that guy was interested
in the property.

281
00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:52.034
there's a possibility
that other developers were. too.

282
00:11:52.036 --> 00:11:55.070
You're wondering if one
of them gaslit the owner.

283
00:11:55.072 --> 00:11:57.606
then killed Boyd.
lest he expose them?

284
00:11:57.608 --> 00:12:00.676
Makes more sense
than ghosts. doesn't it?

285
00:12:00.678 --> 00:12:05.213
<i> Well. I wouldn't say</i>
<i>“ghosts.” plural.</i>

286
00:12:06.250 --> 00:12:08.984
It was my husband. Harry.

287
00:12:08.986 --> 00:12:11.053
I know because
I heard him.

288
00:12:11.055 --> 00:12:12.754
He was talking to me.

289
00:12:14.124 --> 00:12:15.724
Your husband
passed away...?

290
00:12:15.726 --> 00:12:18.460
Oh. coming up
on a year now.

291
00:12:18.462 --> 00:12:20.529
We know that Colin Eisely
made an offer

292
00:12:20.531 --> 00:12:22.364
on the house a few months ago.

293
00:12:22.366 --> 00:12:23.999
Did anyone else approach you?

294
00:12:24.001 --> 00:12:26.435
Yes. once. but-but that was
almost 20 years go.

295
00:12:26.437 --> 00:12:29.337
I don't think that company is
even in business now.

296
00:12:29.339 --> 00:12:32.574
Did you tell anyone else about
the voices you were hearing?

297
00:12:32.576 --> 00:12:34.209
Only my daughter.

298
00:12:34.211 --> 00:12:37.646
She was the one who called
that poor man. Mr. Boyd.

299
00:12:37.648 --> 00:12:41.650
And she wanted him to convince
me that I was imagining things.

300
00:12:41.652 --> 00:12:45.654
She has such
a literal mind.

301
00:12:45.656 --> 00:12:48.156
I've always told her
she should be more open.

302
00:12:48.158 --> 00:12:50.125
So she didn't
hear the voice.

303
00:12:51.428 --> 00:12:54.029
And she never heard any
of Harry's tantrums. either.

304
00:12:54.031 --> 00:12:55.063
Tantrums?

305
00:12:55.065 --> 00:12:57.032
He knocked some glasses

306
00:12:57.034 --> 00:12:58.433
out of that cabinet there.

307
00:12:58.435 --> 00:13:00.068
Lights flickered.

308
00:13:00.070 --> 00:13:02.471
Sometimes. he shook
the whole house.

309
00:13:03.774 --> 00:13:06.842
Oh. he was angry.
and he was letting me know.

310
00:13:06.844 --> 00:13:09.878
And why would he
have been angry?

311
00:13:09.880 --> 00:13:13.749
Sometimes we had
an open marriage.

312
00:13:13.751 --> 00:13:16.651
Other times we didn't.

313
00:13:16.653 --> 00:13:18.186
And when we didn't.

314
00:13:18.188 --> 00:13:20.222
I did some things
that I never told him about.

315
00:13:20.224 --> 00:13:22.457
And now that
he's dead.

316
00:13:22.459 --> 00:13:24.292
he knows everything.

317
00:13:24.294 --> 00:13:26.728
That's quite a one-two punch.
isn't it?

318
00:13:26.730 --> 00:13:29.231
Discovering you're dead
and a cuckold.

319
00:13:29.233 --> 00:13:32.367
It doesn't bother me
that you don't believe me.

320
00:13:32.369 --> 00:13:37.405
I fear that I. too. may be
cursed with a literal mind.

321
00:13:37.407 --> 00:13:40.175
If. however. you are not
experiencing delusions.

322
00:13:40.177 --> 00:13:41.910
it may be possible
that someone is trying

323
00:13:41.912 --> 00:13:43.378
to take advantage of you.

324
00:13:43.380 --> 00:13:46.915
You said Harry spoke to you--
what did he say?

325
00:13:46.917 --> 00:13:49.217
I have it on tape.

326
00:13:49.219 --> 00:13:51.486
You could listen
for yourself.

327
00:13:53.824 --> 00:13:57.292
The clearest I ever heard
Harry's voice was

328
00:13:57.294 --> 00:13:59.094
when I was down here.

329
00:13:59.096 --> 00:14:02.130
so I started leaving my
tape recorder on all the time.

330
00:14:02.132 --> 00:14:06.768
You have to turn the volume all
the way up to hear his voice.

331
00:14:11.275 --> 00:14:12.774
“Imm huh-rahn”?

332
00:14:12.776 --> 00:14:14.176
No. no.

333
00:14:14.178 --> 00:14:15.877
He's saying a name.

334
00:14:15.879 --> 00:14:17.846
Jim Harmon.

335
00:14:17.848 --> 00:14:20.348
That's the man I had
the affair with.

336
00:14:20.350 --> 00:14:22.784
Harry really shook
the whole house that night.

337
00:14:22.786 --> 00:14:26.321
And then he started
yelling Jim's name.

338
00:14:35.032 --> 00:14:37.732
Well. do you still think
I'm imagining things?

339
00:14:37.734 --> 00:14:39.601
I apologize.
Mrs. Renziger.

340
00:14:39.603 --> 00:14:41.736
You most certainly
are not.

341
00:14:41.738 --> 00:14:43.705
You mentioned that some
glasses were knocked

342
00:14:43.707 --> 00:14:45.707
off the cabinet
upstairs.

343
00:14:45.709 --> 00:14:48.210
That cabinet rests
against this wall. yes?

344
00:14:48.212 --> 00:14:49.911
Yes. the living room
is right above it.

345
00:15:04.962 --> 00:15:07.028
How well do you know
your neighbors?

346
00:15:07.030 --> 00:15:08.563
Jerry and Paula?

347
00:15:08.565 --> 00:15:10.832
They moved in here
about the same time as I did.

348
00:15:10.834 --> 00:15:12.667
But they're snowbirds.

349
00:15:12.669 --> 00:15:15.237
They won't be back from Florida
for a few more weeks.

350
00:15:15.239 --> 00:15:19.274
Oh. uh. good neighbors
often exchange keys.

351
00:15:19.276 --> 00:15:21.910
Are you a good neighbor.
Mrs. Renziger?

352
00:15:24.681 --> 00:15:27.148
The voice on the recording
did not say “Jim Harmon”"

353
00:15:27.150 --> 00:15:29.584
it said “im haram”.

354
00:15:29.586 --> 00:15:32.053
It's a common
Arabic obscenity.

355
00:15:32.055 --> 00:15:33.889
So you think
that voice was coming

356
00:15:33.891 --> 00:15:36.258
from all the way over here
in the neighbor's basement.

357
00:15:36.260 --> 00:15:39.527
No. I think someone shortened
the distance considerably.

358
00:15:41.832 --> 00:15:45.367
Along with the voice.
I heard a distinct banging

359
00:15:45.369 --> 00:15:48.336
and a low rumbling
frequency on the recording.

360
00:15:48.338 --> 00:15:51.339
That. along with the rest
of Mrs. Renziger's account.

361
00:15:51.341 --> 00:15:54.776
the. uh. vibrations.
the flickering lights.

362
00:15:54.778 --> 00:15:58.179
all suggest
that someone was employing

363
00:15:58.181 --> 00:16:01.449
digging equipment near
the foundation of her home.

364
00:16:04.054 --> 00:16:06.521
There were no signs
of digging outside.

365
00:16:06.523 --> 00:16:08.757
So you think it was all
happening down here?

366
00:16:24.241 --> 00:16:26.441
Is that a tunnel?

367
00:16:30.347 --> 00:16:32.080
With a termination point

368
00:16:32.082 --> 00:16:35.150
somewhere near the foundation
of Mrs. Renziger's home.

369
00:16:36.320 --> 00:16:37.686
Why would someone
do all this.

370
00:16:37.688 --> 00:16:39.955
dig from this
basement to hers?

371
00:16:40.791 --> 00:16:42.991
I know a way to find out.

372
00:17:03.513 --> 00:17:05.347
Did you find anything?

373
00:17:05.349 --> 00:17:07.482
I have. indeed.

374
00:17:07.484 --> 00:17:12.120
Mrs. Renziger was not visited
by her husband's ghost.

375
00:17:12.122 --> 00:17:15.223
She may. however. have been
visited by terrorists.

376
00:17:27.093 --> 00:17:29.108
Meet “Ruby.”

377
00:17:29.455 --> 00:17:31.488
She's a transatlantic
data cable.

378
00:17:31.490 --> 00:17:33.323
The fastest
in the world

379
00:17:33.325 --> 00:17:36.526
and a backbone of the
North American Internet.

380
00:17:36.528 --> 00:17:37.794
She looks like
a garden hose.

381
00:17:37.796 --> 00:17:39.429
It's a curse
of the modern age

382
00:17:39.431 --> 00:17:41.265
that very significant things
appear commonplace.

383
00:17:41.267 --> 00:17:43.700
Now. Ruby is one of
several undersea cables

384
00:17:43.702 --> 00:17:46.270
which connects Europe
to the United States.

385
00:17:46.272 --> 00:17:49.306
The full spectrum of commerce
and communication flows

386
00:17:49.308 --> 00:17:51.108
through her optic fibers.

387
00:17:51.110 --> 00:17:54.011
as well as the requisite glut
of pornography and cat videos.

388
00:17:54.013 --> 00:17:57.614
And you knew that was
what that cable was how?

389
00:17:57.616 --> 00:18:00.017
The location of such
cables is mapped.

390
00:18:00.019 --> 00:18:02.853
They're accessible
with very little effort.

391
00:18:02.855 --> 00:18:05.856
The intent is to avoid
entanglements

392
00:18:05.858 --> 00:18:08.859
and utility mishaps.
but it also makes them

393
00:18:08.861 --> 00:18:12.296
amongst the most vulnerable
terrorist targets in the world.

394
00:18:12.298 --> 00:18:15.365
And this basement's probably a
pretty smart place to dig from.

395
00:18:15.367 --> 00:18:17.801
And anywhere along the beach
would attract attention.

396
00:18:17.803 --> 00:18:19.670
out in the ocean would
be a lot harder.

397
00:18:19.672 --> 00:18:21.538
And the cable ties
into a landing house

398
00:18:21.540 --> 00:18:22.973
another quarter
of a mile inland.

399
00:18:22.975 --> 00:18:25.509
at which point security
increases markedly.

400
00:18:25.511 --> 00:18:27.077
What our attackers did not
account for was

401
00:18:27.079 --> 00:18:28.845
the intrusion of Garrison Boyd.

402
00:18:28.847 --> 00:18:31.214
Right. so someone runs
tunneling equipment

403
00:18:31.216 --> 00:18:33.483
out of the Ayers' basement while
they're away for the winter.

404
00:18:33.485 --> 00:18:35.485
Mrs. Renziger
hears the noise

405
00:18:35.487 --> 00:18:36.987
and thinks it's
her dead husband.

406
00:18:36.989 --> 00:18:38.922
so her daughter asks
Boyd to prove otherwise.

407
00:18:38.924 --> 00:18:41.591
and then Boyd finds all this.
same way you and Joan did?

408
00:18:47.399 --> 00:18:49.333
This little fella was

409
00:18:49.335 --> 00:18:51.401
amongst the gardening
equipment over there.

410
00:18:51.403 --> 00:18:53.270
The tip of his hat is missing.

411
00:18:56.275 --> 00:18:58.342
Mr. Boyd was murdered
in this room.

412
00:18:58.344 --> 00:19:01.178
The killer loads the body
into Boyd's car.

413
00:19:01.180 --> 00:19:03.213
drives it back into the city.
but then what?

414
00:19:03.215 --> 00:19:05.515
Why not come back
and cut the cable?

415
00:19:05.517 --> 00:19:08.251
Figured Boyd found them. someone
else might be coming. too?

416
00:19:08.253 --> 00:19:09.286
Perhaps.

417
00:19:09.288 --> 00:19:10.454
Or perhaps the fact

418
00:19:10.456 --> 00:19:12.055
that Ruby has not been cut

419
00:19:12.057 --> 00:19:13.991
signals a much greater threat.

420
00:19:15.027 --> 00:19:16.994
The Internet is designed
with redundancies.

421
00:19:16.996 --> 00:19:19.896
Cutting a single cable would
no doubt cause some problems.

422
00:19:19.898 --> 00:19:21.798
but a coordinated attack.

423
00:19:21.800 --> 00:19:23.533
that could be crippling.

424
00:19:23.535 --> 00:19:26.370
You think there might be other
guys digging up other cables.

425
00:19:26.372 --> 00:19:28.739
waiting for a signal to
cut them all at once?

426
00:19:28.741 --> 00:19:31.441
I think it's a possibility
that we should consider.

427
00:19:31.443 --> 00:19:32.542
I'll reach out to DHS.

428
00:19:32.544 --> 00:19:35.846
Let them know
what's going on.

429
00:19:42.054 --> 00:19:43.587
I'll check back with you.

430
00:19:45.157 --> 00:19:46.556
So. you were right.

431
00:19:46.558 --> 00:19:48.725
Whoever dug that tunnel stuck
mostly to the basement.

432
00:19:48.727 --> 00:19:50.494
But they did come up here
every now and then.

433
00:19:50.496 --> 00:19:52.095
Yes. naturally.

434
00:19:52.097 --> 00:19:54.498
If the man or men or women
were here to do arduous work.

435
00:19:54.500 --> 00:19:55.932
the hours would have
been long.

436
00:19:55.934 --> 00:19:57.768
They would have needed
to eat. hydrate

437
00:19:57.770 --> 00:19:59.436
and. of course.
expel waste.

438
00:19:59.438 --> 00:20:01.038
Toilet seat was up.
so I'm guessing

439
00:20:01.040 --> 00:20:02.506
at least one
person was a “he”"

440
00:20:02.508 --> 00:20:05.776
Also we found this
in the fridge.

441
00:20:06.779 --> 00:20:08.845
“Doogh.”

442
00:20:08.847 --> 00:20:12.282
Carbonated yogurt drink
popular in Arab countries.

443
00:20:12.284 --> 00:20:14.751
It's hard to believe bubbling
yogurt is popular anywhere.

444
00:20:14.753 --> 00:20:16.386
I figured it didn't
belong to the Ayers.

445
00:20:16.388 --> 00:20:17.821
so I called the
American distributor.

446
00:20:17.823 --> 00:20:19.489
No place on the
island sells it.

447
00:20:19.491 --> 00:20:20.891
Six stores in
the city do.

448
00:20:20.893 --> 00:20:23.326
They're e-mailing
me a list.

449
00:20:23.328 --> 00:20:25.328
So assuming these stores
have surveillance cameras.

450
00:20:25.330 --> 00:20:28.298
we can check their footage
from the last few weeks.

451
00:20:28.300 --> 00:20:30.667
see if anyone
jumps out.

452
00:20:30.669 --> 00:20:32.769
<i> Hannah. come in.</i>

453
00:20:36.809 --> 00:20:38.608
So I have good news.

454
00:20:38.610 --> 00:20:40.377
Don't tell me
you solved it already.

455
00:20:40.379 --> 00:20:42.813
Actually. you already
had all the pieces.

456
00:20:42.815 --> 00:20:44.714
Now. you said that all three
drugstores were robbed

457
00:20:44.716 --> 00:20:46.249
around closing time.

458
00:20:46.251 --> 00:20:48.585
At first. I assumed
what you probably did.

459
00:20:48.587 --> 00:20:51.621
That it was because closing is
when a store is most vulnerable.

460
00:20:51.623 --> 00:20:54.558
No customers. fewer employees.
most cash on hand.

461
00:20:54.560 --> 00:20:57.427
But in this case. there
was something else.

462
00:20:57.429 --> 00:20:59.429
Now. two of the
pharmacists told you

463
00:20:59.431 --> 00:21:00.997
that a candy machine
vendor had come by

464
00:21:00.999 --> 00:21:02.666
just before
the robberies.

465
00:21:02.668 --> 00:21:04.634
I checked.

466
00:21:04.636 --> 00:21:07.237
and that same vendor has
machines in all three stores.

467
00:21:07.239 --> 00:21:08.872
You think the vendor's
in on it.

468
00:21:08.874 --> 00:21:10.307
He scopes out
the stores

469
00:21:10.309 --> 00:21:12.309
and then tells his accomplices
if it's all clear.

470
00:21:12.311 --> 00:21:15.212
A friend took these today.

471
00:21:15.214 --> 00:21:17.914
Vending machine company
uses this warehouse

472
00:21:17.916 --> 00:21:19.850
to store their inventory
and do repairs.

473
00:21:19.852 --> 00:21:21.084
Look at these guys.

474
00:21:21.086 --> 00:21:24.321
Height. hair color.
visible tattoos.

475
00:21:24.323 --> 00:21:27.390
They match the descriptions
of the three perps.

476
00:21:27.392 --> 00:21:30.193
They definitely don't look like
they're in the gumball business.

477
00:21:30.195 --> 00:21:31.428
Hmm.

478
00:21:31.430 --> 00:21:32.662
You found them.

479
00:21:32.664 --> 00:21:33.897
I can't believe it.

480
00:21:33.899 --> 00:21:35.398
I mean. I-I can.
I'm not surprised.

481
00:21:35.400 --> 00:21:36.666
But thank you.

482
00:21:36.668 --> 00:21:38.768
Odds are.

483
00:21:38.770 --> 00:21:40.337
this is where they're storing
the stolen pills.

484
00:21:40.339 --> 00:21:42.272
When you bring this
to Detective Hanford.

485
00:21:42.274 --> 00:21:43.874
feel free to leave
my name out of it.

486
00:21:43.876 --> 00:21:45.308
But my guess is. the
department's gonna want

487
00:21:45.310 --> 00:21:47.844
to sit on this place for a while.
Why?

488
00:21:47.846 --> 00:21:49.379
As long as it
doesn't look like

489
00:21:49.381 --> 00:21:50.847
another robbery
is imminent.

490
00:21:50.849 --> 00:21:52.349
they're gonna want
to follow the drugs

491
00:21:52.351 --> 00:21:54.718
up the food chain.
With the amount of pills

492
00:21:54.720 --> 00:21:56.887
these guys are stealing. they
probably have help moving them.

493
00:21:56.889 --> 00:22:00.090
So this could lead
to bigger fish.

494
00:22:05.297 --> 00:22:07.864
It took no small amount
of negotiation. but I was able

495
00:22:07.866 --> 00:22:10.300
to procure security footage
from each of the Doogh-selling

496
00:22:10.302 --> 00:22:12.102
ethnic markets
that you identified.

497
00:22:12.104 --> 00:22:14.304
Now. taking into account
the hours Claire Renziger

498
00:22:14.306 --> 00:22:16.773
did and did not hear “ghosts.”

499
00:22:16.775 --> 00:22:18.575
it would appear
that our tunneler kept hours

500
00:22:18.577 --> 00:22:20.210
between 8:00 to 6:00.

501
00:22:20.212 --> 00:22:22.379
So it stands to reason
that he bought his Doogh

502
00:22:22.381 --> 00:22:23.847
and other provisions
at either the beginning

503
00:22:23.849 --> 00:22:25.081
or the end of each day.

504
00:22:25.083 --> 00:22:27.484
Oh. that's great.

505
00:22:27.486 --> 00:22:29.286
It'll help us move
through these faster.

506
00:22:29.288 --> 00:22:31.588
Assuming. of course. you're not
still splitting your time

507
00:22:31.590 --> 00:22:33.089
between the tribulations
of a beat cop

508
00:22:33.091 --> 00:22:34.724
and the hunt
for a likely terrorist.

509
00:22:34.726 --> 00:22:37.627
May I remind you that “beat co”"
is our boss's daughter?

510
00:22:37.629 --> 00:22:38.995
Is that why
you were helping her?

511
00:22:38.997 --> 00:22:40.263
To curry favor?

512
00:22:40.265 --> 00:22:42.332
I'm helping her
because she asked me.

513
00:22:42.334 --> 00:22:44.334
What do you think of her?

514
00:22:44.336 --> 00:22:45.669
Hannah?

515
00:22:45.671 --> 00:22:47.237
She's nice.

516
00:22:47.239 --> 00:22:49.372
I mean. what do you think of her
as an investigator?

517
00:22:49.374 --> 00:22:51.174
Oh. she's green.

518
00:22:51.176 --> 00:22:52.609
I mean. she's
dedicated.

519
00:22:52.611 --> 00:22:53.677
She did all the legwork.

520
00:22:53.679 --> 00:22:54.711
she just couldn't
connect all the dots.

521
00:22:54.713 --> 00:22:56.313
Why?
Oh. it just confirms

522
00:22:56.315 --> 00:22:57.614
a long-held suspicion.

523
00:22:57.616 --> 00:22:58.882
She's middling

524
00:22:58.884 --> 00:23:00.884
Hold on. I did not say
she was “middling.”

525
00:23:00.886 --> 00:23:02.986
And that's sad. because she is
the daughter of a colleague

526
00:23:02.988 --> 00:23:05.522
and he has certain aspirations for her.
Excuse me.

527
00:23:05.524 --> 00:23:07.457
but have you ever
even talked to Hannah?

528
00:23:07.459 --> 00:23:09.125
Twice.
That's it?

529
00:23:09.127 --> 00:23:10.493
And that all you needed
to size her up?

530
00:23:10.495 --> 00:23:12.162
I also looked at her records.

531
00:23:12.164 --> 00:23:13.763
Understand. Watson:

532
00:23:13.765 --> 00:23:15.565
I think she's a perfectly
capable police officer.

533
00:23:15.567 --> 00:23:17.467
She knows how to handle herself
in a confrontation

534
00:23:17.469 --> 00:23:19.269
and she's first-rate
with a weapon.

535
00:23:19.271 --> 00:23:21.371
What I fear she is not. however.
is a detective.

536
00:23:21.373 --> 00:23:22.973
Give me a break.

537
00:23:22.975 --> 00:23:24.140
It's a calling. Watson;

538
00:23:24.142 --> 00:23:25.375
no one knows that
better than you.

539
00:23:25.377 --> 00:23:27.277
I learned because you taught me.

540
00:23:27.279 --> 00:23:28.979
I taught you
because I saw something.

541
00:23:28.981 --> 00:23:31.281
What if I told you
I see something in Hannah?

542
00:23:31.283 --> 00:23:32.816
I would tell you
you're mistaken.

543
00:23:32.818 --> 00:23:34.117
You know what?

544
00:23:34.119 --> 00:23:35.919
I'll be in my room.

545
00:23:57.476 --> 00:23:59.309
Thought I'd let you sleep in.

546
00:23:59.311 --> 00:24:01.244
You found my notes?

547
00:24:01.246 --> 00:24:03.680
Well. sort of
hard to miss.

548
00:24:03.682 --> 00:24:05.815
Watched the video?

549
00:24:05.817 --> 00:24:07.250
I take it this is our suspect?

550
00:24:07.252 --> 00:24:08.752
Note the coveralls.

551
00:24:08.754 --> 00:24:10.120
The tape your watching

552
00:24:10.122 --> 00:24:14.124
records his fifth appearance
at the store

553
00:24:14.126 --> 00:24:15.659
in a span of two weeks.

554
00:24:15.661 --> 00:24:17.494
During that period of time.

555
00:24:17.496 --> 00:24:19.462
his clothes get
progressively dirtier.

556
00:24:19.464 --> 00:24:22.098
save for two rectangular spots
on his knees.

557
00:24:22.100 --> 00:24:23.767
Presumably.
he wore some knee pads

558
00:24:23.769 --> 00:24:25.001
while he was digging his tunnel.

559
00:24:25.003 --> 00:24:27.170
Well presumably
isn't “definitely.”

560
00:24:27.172 --> 00:24:28.872
He may just be a plumber.

561
00:24:28.874 --> 00:24:30.607
And I see he didn't
use his credit card.

562
00:24:30.609 --> 00:24:32.676
As is his wont. Unfortunately.
he can't be identified

563
00:24:32.678 --> 00:24:33.943
via receipts.

564
00:24:33.945 --> 00:24:35.145
The woman in the red coat.
however...

565
00:24:35.147 --> 00:24:37.047
She knows him.

566
00:24:37.049 --> 00:24:38.948
She paid with
her American Express.

567
00:24:38.950 --> 00:24:40.550
Her name is Yolanda Massee

568
00:24:40.552 --> 00:24:43.053
and I'm stepping
into her elevator as we speak.

569
00:24:43.055 --> 00:24:46.156
I'll call you when I know more.

570
00:24:50.062 --> 00:24:51.594
Yes?

571
00:24:51.596 --> 00:24:52.962
Hello. Ms. Massee?

572
00:24:52.964 --> 00:24:54.564
My name is Sherlock Holmes.

573
00:24:54.566 --> 00:24:56.533
I'm a consultant with
the New York Police Department.

574
00:24:56.535 --> 00:24:58.234
I was hoping I might
ask you a few questions.

575
00:24:58.236 --> 00:24:59.369
Do you have a badge?

576
00:24:59.371 --> 00:25:00.570
I'm afraid I'm quite allergic

577
00:25:00.572 --> 00:25:02.405
to iconography.
I was just--

578
00:25:02.407 --> 00:25:04.207
I was hoping you might be able
to tell me this man's name.

579
00:25:04.209 --> 00:25:06.042
Is this a joke?

580
00:25:06.044 --> 00:25:07.877
No.

581
00:25:07.879 --> 00:25:10.280
I think it's Nazim or Nadim...

582
00:25:10.282 --> 00:25:11.548
I'm not really sure.

583
00:25:11.550 --> 00:25:12.816
But you know him?

584
00:25:12.818 --> 00:25:14.084
I don't know.

585
00:25:14.086 --> 00:25:15.618
How well do you know
your neighbors?

586
00:25:15.620 --> 00:25:16.820
He's your neighbor?

587
00:25:16.822 --> 00:25:18.321
He lives right there.

588
00:25:26.832 --> 00:25:28.932
I'd recommend you leave
your building right now.

589
00:25:28.934 --> 00:25:30.367
What? Why?

590
00:25:30.369 --> 00:25:32.135
'Cause your neighbor
heard us talking...

591
00:25:33.605 --> 00:25:35.138
...and he is currently dousing

592
00:25:35.140 --> 00:25:36.906
his apartment with accelerant.

593
00:25:36.908 --> 00:25:38.341
Go on!

594
00:25:41.146 --> 00:25:44.114
Nadim? Or is it Nazim?

595
00:25:44.116 --> 00:25:45.415
You might find this
hard to believe.

596
00:25:45.417 --> 00:25:46.783
but I'm I'm actually
here to help you.

597
00:25:46.785 --> 00:25:48.051
Don't come any closer.

598
00:25:50.322 --> 00:25:51.721
You're not a terrorist at all.
are you?

599
00:25:51.723 --> 00:25:52.956
No.

600
00:25:52.958 --> 00:25:54.958
Look. I'm open
to the possibility

601
00:25:54.960 --> 00:25:56.760
that Garrison Boyd's death
was an accident.

602
00:25:56.762 --> 00:25:59.362
He caught you unawares
and-and you panicked.

603
00:25:59.364 --> 00:26:01.131
But if you drop that lighter.

604
00:26:01.133 --> 00:26:04.000
you will be attempting murder
on the 200 or so other people

605
00:26:04.002 --> 00:26:05.435
who live in this building.

606
00:26:25.756 --> 00:26:27.911
This...

607
00:26:27.913 --> 00:26:29.934
this contraption
was at the heart

608
00:26:29.935 --> 00:26:32.469
of the drawings
on Nadim Al-Haj's walls.

609
00:26:32.471 --> 00:26:34.905
<i>I only had a moment</i>
<i>to absorb them before they were</i>

610
00:26:34.907 --> 00:26:36.273
engulfed in flames.

611
00:26:36.275 --> 00:26:39.043
but it was clear
that he never intended

612
00:26:39.045 --> 00:26:40.577
to sever the cable
that he excavated.

613
00:26:40.579 --> 00:26:42.079
Rather. I think
his plan was

614
00:26:42.081 --> 00:26:44.848
to splice this device onto it.

615
00:26:46.252 --> 00:26:47.851
You think you can figure out
what it does?

616
00:26:47.853 --> 00:26:50.054
I won't know for sure till
we cut off the melted plastic.

617
00:26:50.056 --> 00:26:52.990
but hopefully. enough of the
circuitry inside is intact.

618
00:26:52.992 --> 00:26:54.558
If I was a betting man.

619
00:26:54.560 --> 00:26:56.427
I'd say that it was meant
to collect information

620
00:26:56.429 --> 00:26:57.928
and transmit it elsewhere.

621
00:26:57.930 --> 00:27:00.197
You're thinking this is
one big data grab.

622
00:27:00.199 --> 00:27:01.699
Why not hack into it

623
00:27:01.701 --> 00:27:03.467
from a computer somewhere?

624
00:27:03.469 --> 00:27:04.935
There's gotta be an easier way
than digging that tunnel.

625
00:27:04.937 --> 00:27:06.603
Ask the NSA.

626
00:27:06.605 --> 00:27:07.838
According to Edward Snowden.

627
00:27:07.840 --> 00:27:09.139
U.S. intelligence agencies

628
00:27:09.141 --> 00:27:10.607
routinely tap into these cables

629
00:27:10.609 --> 00:27:12.076
upstream of their
official tie-ins

630
00:27:12.078 --> 00:27:13.877
so they can better monitor
American citizens.

631
00:27:13.879 --> 00:27:15.646
The first time Ruby
feeds aboveground

632
00:27:15.648 --> 00:27:17.381
is at 60 Hudson.
downtown.

633
00:27:17.383 --> 00:27:19.817
Big banks have a offices there
to get financial data first.

634
00:27:19.819 --> 00:27:21.685
but it's also where a lot
of info gets encrypted

635
00:27:21.687 --> 00:27:22.920
and after that.

636
00:27:22.922 --> 00:27:24.855
it's harder to spy on.

637
00:27:24.857 --> 00:27:26.457
Actually. digging a hole
on Long Island

638
00:27:26.459 --> 00:27:28.225
- makes a lot of sense.
- So you're saying

639
00:27:28.227 --> 00:27:29.893
So you're saying my phone
might ring at any minute.

640
00:27:29.895 --> 00:27:31.995
telling me this guy
works for our government?

641
00:27:31.997 --> 00:27:34.398
Perhaps. Or a foreign one.
Or a corporation.

642
00:27:34.400 --> 00:27:35.699
I mean. who in this day and age

643
00:27:35.701 --> 00:27:37.067
does<i> not</i> view information
as power?

644
00:27:37.069 --> 00:27:38.736
Hopefully. the device

645
00:27:38.738 --> 00:27:40.671
will tell us what information
the perp was capturing:

646
00:27:40.673 --> 00:27:42.740
e-mails. trade secrets.
credit card numbers...

647
00:27:42.742 --> 00:27:44.742
If we're lucky.
we'll even get an IP address

648
00:27:44.744 --> 00:27:46.143
where it was being sent.

649
00:27:46.145 --> 00:27:48.245
Then we'll have
a better idea of what

650
00:27:48.247 --> 00:27:49.780
we're dealing with.

651
00:27:49.782 --> 00:27:52.983
Nadim Al-Haj. born
in Iraq in 1978.

652
00:27:52.985 --> 00:27:55.252
He emigrated to the U.S. in '06

653
00:27:55.254 --> 00:27:57.721
and became a citizen
two years ago.

654
00:27:57.723 --> 00:28:00.290
He was an electrical engineer
in his country.

655
00:28:00.292 --> 00:28:02.659
but he's been working here as
a lineman for the cable company.

656
00:28:02.661 --> 00:28:04.328
So he definitely
had the skills.

657
00:28:04.330 --> 00:28:06.296
Yeah. a few
parking summonses.

658
00:28:06.298 --> 00:28:09.500
but no criminal record
that I could find.

659
00:28:09.502 --> 00:28:11.402
What's that about?

660
00:28:11.404 --> 00:28:13.003
Oh. you didn't hear?

661
00:28:13.005 --> 00:28:14.671
Hannah made
a big collar

662
00:28:14.673 --> 00:28:16.240
on her patrol this morning.

663
00:28:16.242 --> 00:28:17.708
Everyone's been messing
with the captain over it.

664
00:28:17.710 --> 00:28:19.610
Hmm. What'd she do?

665
00:28:19.612 --> 00:28:21.111
She spotted a perp
who matched the description

666
00:28:21.113 --> 00:28:23.046
off a few drugstore robberies
on her beat.

667
00:28:23.048 --> 00:28:24.982
Now. he took off
into a warehouse.

668
00:28:24.984 --> 00:28:27.284
she and her partner followed.
scooped him up

669
00:28:27.286 --> 00:28:30.554
and found almost
200 grand worth of pills.

670
00:28:30.556 --> 00:28:32.122
That's pretty lucky.

671
00:28:32.124 --> 00:28:34.324
Well. that ain't luck.
That's DNA.

672
00:28:34.326 --> 00:28:36.693
She's good.

673
00:28:36.695 --> 00:28:38.829
I-- you know.
I just realized I forgot--

674
00:28:38.831 --> 00:28:40.330
I have to run an errand.

675
00:28:40.332 --> 00:28:41.865
I'll... just tell Sherlock
I'll catch up.

676
00:28:41.867 --> 00:28:43.300
All right.

677
00:28:46.972 --> 00:28:48.338
Captain...

678
00:28:48.340 --> 00:28:50.474
this is all we could find
on Nadim Al-Haj.

679
00:28:50.476 --> 00:28:52.176
It isn't much.

680
00:28:52.178 --> 00:28:54.511
Finest message is out
on him and his van.

681
00:28:54.513 --> 00:28:56.513
and Homeland Security's
issued a BOLO

682
00:28:56.515 --> 00:28:58.749
to Port Authority.
Amtrak and TSA.

683
00:28:58.751 --> 00:29:00.784
The apartment
Mr. Al-Haj occupied

684
00:29:00.786 --> 00:29:02.820
is owned by
“The Collin Eisely Group”?

685
00:29:03.622 --> 00:29:05.756
You know that name?
I do.

686
00:29:05.758 --> 00:29:08.158
Watson and I paid a visit
to Collin Eisely yesterday.

687
00:29:08.160 --> 00:29:09.660
He's a developer.

688
00:29:09.662 --> 00:29:11.528
Several months ago.
he made a bid on the house

689
00:29:11.530 --> 00:29:13.263
next to the one with the tunnel.

690
00:29:13.265 --> 00:29:17.167
You mean the one that's actually
much closer to the cable?

691
00:29:17.169 --> 00:29:19.670
<i>The man who murdered</i>
<i>Garrison Boyd</i>

692
00:29:19.672 --> 00:29:21.505
lives in a building
that you own.

693
00:29:21.507 --> 00:29:22.773
What do you suppose

694
00:29:22.775 --> 00:29:25.709
the odds are of that
being a coincidence?

695
00:29:25.711 --> 00:29:27.077
I own several buildings.

696
00:29:27.079 --> 00:29:29.346
which. together.
house hundreds of tenants.

697
00:29:29.348 --> 00:29:31.081
It may surprise you to know

698
00:29:31.083 --> 00:29:32.850
that I'm not on a first-name
basis with any of them.

699
00:29:32.852 --> 00:29:34.351
It's interesting that
you should mention names.

700
00:29:34.353 --> 00:29:35.886
because you changed yours.
did you not?

701
00:29:35.888 --> 00:29:38.222
Before you got
into real estate.

702
00:29:38.224 --> 00:29:40.791
you were a stockbroker.
and until a few years ago.

703
00:29:40.793 --> 00:29:42.459
your legal name
was Louis Eisely.

704
00:29:42.461 --> 00:29:44.394
Collin was your middle name.

705
00:29:44.396 --> 00:29:46.597
Now. we're guessing the
decision to change it

706
00:29:46.599 --> 00:29:47.965
has something
to do with you

707
00:29:47.967 --> 00:29:49.299
serving 18 months
for insider trading?

708
00:29:49.301 --> 00:29:51.668
The name change was aboveboard;

709
00:29:51.670 --> 00:29:54.271
I'm not breaking any laws.

710
00:29:54.273 --> 00:29:56.540
My real estate dealings
go much more smoothly

711
00:29:56.542 --> 00:29:58.041
when my criminal record

712
00:29:58.043 --> 00:29:59.576
isn't the first thing
people learn about me.

713
00:29:59.578 --> 00:30:01.311
I imagine they would.

714
00:30:01.313 --> 00:30:04.314
Because<i> Louis</i> Eisely
was a particularly cutthroat

715
00:30:04.316 --> 00:30:05.849
Wall Street trader.

716
00:30:05.851 --> 00:30:07.651
From the early 2000s.

717
00:30:07.653 --> 00:30:09.887
A man whose downfall.
at the height of his career.

718
00:30:09.889 --> 00:30:13.323
made his name synonymous
with Wall Street greed.

719
00:30:14.360 --> 00:30:16.326
I did my time.

720
00:30:16.328 --> 00:30:17.895
Prison changed me.

721
00:30:17.897 --> 00:30:20.330
I'm not so sure
that it did.

722
00:30:20.332 --> 00:30:22.666
Trading in secrets
put you on top.

723
00:30:22.668 --> 00:30:25.435
Does a man like you ever
really lose a taste for that?

724
00:30:25.437 --> 00:30:29.973
You still haven't explained
what it is you think I did.

725
00:30:29.975 --> 00:30:31.508
You hired Nadim Al-Haj

726
00:30:31.510 --> 00:30:34.645
to tap a transatlantic
data cable called Ruby.

727
00:30:34.647 --> 00:30:37.080
Runs right past
Claire Renziger's basement.

728
00:30:37.082 --> 00:30:39.550
So. first. you tried
to buy her house.

729
00:30:39.552 --> 00:30:40.817
When she turned you down.

730
00:30:40.819 --> 00:30:42.686
you had Al-Haj dig a tunnel

731
00:30:42.688 --> 00:30:44.087
from next door. instead.

732
00:30:45.190 --> 00:30:47.724
And why would I have done
any of that?

733
00:30:47.726 --> 00:30:48.992
Because you have
a savant's talent

734
00:30:48.994 --> 00:30:50.561
for turning information
into gold.

735
00:30:50.563 --> 00:30:52.362
Ruby is the mother lode.

736
00:30:52.364 --> 00:30:54.398
Tapping into her would give you
unfettered access

737
00:30:54.400 --> 00:30:55.933
to a wealth of intelligence

738
00:30:55.935 --> 00:30:57.868
with which to inform
your investment strategies.

739
00:30:57.870 --> 00:30:59.503
That's actually brilliant.

740
00:30:59.505 --> 00:31:00.971
I wish I had thought of it

741
00:31:00.973 --> 00:31:02.372
back when I was trading.

742
00:31:02.374 --> 00:31:04.274
I can't go near the market.

743
00:31:04.276 --> 00:31:07.878
The FCC has banned me from
trading until the day I die.

744
00:31:07.880 --> 00:31:10.480
By court order.
every dollar I have in stocks

745
00:31:10.482 --> 00:31:12.516
is in a blind trust.
You can look it up.

746
00:31:12.518 --> 00:31:14.952
Well. perhaps you're selling
the information for a price.

747
00:31:14.954 --> 00:31:16.820
And keep the proceeds where?

748
00:31:16.822 --> 00:31:18.088
In my mattress?

749
00:31:18.090 --> 00:31:20.057
The Feds audit all my accounts.

750
00:31:20.059 --> 00:31:22.459
I can't win at bingo
without them taking notice.

751
00:31:23.929 --> 00:31:25.896
Gentlemen.

752
00:31:25.898 --> 00:31:28.599
I have more important things
to do with my day.

753
00:31:28.601 --> 00:31:30.100
You're fishing;

754
00:31:30.102 --> 00:31:32.669
I'm not biting.

755
00:31:35.007 --> 00:31:37.608
Hannah.

756
00:31:37.610 --> 00:31:39.843
I just heard
the news.

757
00:31:39.845 --> 00:31:41.378
Congratulations.

758
00:31:41.380 --> 00:31:43.146
Thanks.

759
00:31:43.148 --> 00:31:44.514
So. I thought it was interesting

760
00:31:44.516 --> 00:31:46.750
how you just happened
to spot the suspect.

761
00:31:46.752 --> 00:31:48.285
took a whole stash house down.

762
00:31:48.287 --> 00:31:49.553
You said to leave
you out of it.

763
00:31:49.555 --> 00:31:51.254
This is not about
credit. Hannah.

764
00:31:51.256 --> 00:31:52.656
This is about
doing the right thing.

765
00:31:52.658 --> 00:31:55.325
The right thing would've
been to kick it upstairs.

766
00:31:55.327 --> 00:31:57.127
Let Hanford take it from there.

767
00:31:57.129 --> 00:31:59.296
Right. Go after bigger fish.

768
00:31:59.298 --> 00:32:00.263
So. why didn't you?

769
00:32:00.265 --> 00:32:01.498
You and I both know

770
00:32:01.500 --> 00:32:03.066
if I turned this
over to Hanford.

771
00:32:03.068 --> 00:32:04.635
I would've ended up a
footnote in his report.

772
00:32:04.637 --> 00:32:06.603
If it did lead to bigger
fish. not even that.

773
00:32:06.605 --> 00:32:09.106
But you don't know that.
I do. 'Cause I'm a cop.

774
00:32:09.108 --> 00:32:10.807
I've seen it.
I know how it works.

775
00:32:12.244 --> 00:32:13.610
And I'm not a cop. right?

776
00:32:13.612 --> 00:32:15.145
It's just different for me.

777
00:32:15.147 --> 00:32:16.313
Sergeant's exam is coming up.

778
00:32:16.315 --> 00:32:18.081
I get extra points
for commendations.

779
00:32:18.083 --> 00:32:20.217
I thought you were doing this
to help the people on your beat.

780
00:32:20.219 --> 00:32:23.120
Or is that just something
you thought I wanted to hear?

781
00:32:23.122 --> 00:32:24.488
I did help them.

782
00:32:24.490 --> 00:32:26.289
I got some bad guys
off the street.

783
00:32:26.291 --> 00:32:28.091
Just not as many
as you could have.

784
00:32:28.093 --> 00:32:30.794
You helped me
when I needed help.

785
00:32:30.796 --> 00:32:33.497
I won't forget it.

786
00:32:40.105 --> 00:32:42.639
Hey. I just ran

787
00:32:42.641 --> 00:32:44.775
into Marcus downstairs.
He told me about Collin Eisley.

788
00:32:44.777 --> 00:32:46.209
Sounds like it didn't go well.

789
00:32:46.211 --> 00:32:48.045
I'm no less convinced
of his connection

790
00:32:48.047 --> 00:32:49.680
to Garrison Boyd's murder.

791
00:32:49.682 --> 00:32:51.314
You know.
because of his history.

792
00:32:51.316 --> 00:32:53.850
Mr. Eisley's money
is in a blind trust.

793
00:32:53.852 --> 00:32:55.752
Well. that means
he can't touch it. right?

794
00:32:55.754 --> 00:32:59.089
More than that-- he can't
even know how it's managed.

795
00:32:59.091 --> 00:33:02.292
Now. Eisley's trust is handled
by Robiskie Investments.

796
00:33:02.294 --> 00:33:04.828
a second-tier
brokerage house at best.

797
00:33:04.830 --> 00:33:07.064
I suspect more prominent firms
refused his business

798
00:33:07.066 --> 00:33:09.833
because of the miasma
that still surrounds him.

799
00:33:09.835 --> 00:33:13.136
His investments are all
in computer-traded funds.

800
00:33:13.138 --> 00:33:17.007
which deliver a return far less
than the profits he once made.

801
00:33:17.009 --> 00:33:18.408
That's got to burn.

802
00:33:18.410 --> 00:33:19.609
Indeed.

803
00:33:19.611 --> 00:33:21.111
A man who had spent
his entire life

804
00:33:21.113 --> 00:33:22.946
exploiting weaknesses
in the financial system

805
00:33:22.948 --> 00:33:25.615
would surely chafe
at such restrictions.

806
00:33:25.617 --> 00:33:27.117
So. you thought he
wanted to tap into Ruby

807
00:33:27.119 --> 00:33:28.618
in order to profit
off the information.

808
00:33:28.620 --> 00:33:30.554
but there's no way he
can profit from it.

809
00:33:30.556 --> 00:33:32.689
Or that I've found thus far.
But I'm confident that when TARU

810
00:33:32.691 --> 00:33:35.158
deliver its report.
that mystery box is

811
00:33:35.160 --> 00:33:37.561
gonna connect Eisley
to the crime.

812
00:33:37.563 --> 00:33:39.229
In the meantime...

813
00:33:39.231 --> 00:33:42.666
I found this.

814
00:33:42.668 --> 00:33:44.701
A decade ago.
when Western companies

815
00:33:44.703 --> 00:33:47.971
were pillaging Iraq's resources
in the name of reconstruction.

816
00:33:47.973 --> 00:33:50.507
Eisley toured the oil fields

817
00:33:50.509 --> 00:33:51.875
near Kirkuk.

818
00:33:51.877 --> 00:33:53.410
That's Nadim Al-Haj.

819
00:33:53.412 --> 00:33:54.945
Al-Haj was his driver.

820
00:33:54.947 --> 00:33:56.046
He subsequently sponsored

821
00:33:56.048 --> 00:33:58.682
his immigration into the U.S.

822
00:33:58.684 --> 00:34:00.650
Now. “lived in his building”
could be written off to chance.

823
00:34:00.652 --> 00:34:02.753
This cannot.

824
00:34:02.755 --> 00:34:05.756
Hey. a senior technician
from TARU is on his way up.

825
00:34:05.758 --> 00:34:08.325
Says he's got some news.

826
00:34:10.395 --> 00:34:12.195
Parts of it were
pretty badly fused.

827
00:34:12.197 --> 00:34:14.064
but we were able
to forensically reconstruct

828
00:34:14.066 --> 00:34:16.366
most of the circuitry.
And?

829
00:34:16.368 --> 00:34:18.201
It doesn't look
like it was meant

830
00:34:18.203 --> 00:34:20.403
to transmit anything anywhere.

831
00:34:20.405 --> 00:34:22.439
So. what was it supposed to do?

832
00:34:22.441 --> 00:34:23.974
Well. that's the thing.
It doesn't store anything.

833
00:34:23.976 --> 00:34:25.275
It doesn't re-route anything.

834
00:34:25.277 --> 00:34:26.476
It doesn't change anything.

835
00:34:26.478 --> 00:34:28.912
It's just a maze of circuits.

836
00:34:28.914 --> 00:34:31.214
Data goes in one end
and comes out the other.

837
00:34:31.216 --> 00:34:33.550
That's it.

838
00:34:33.552 --> 00:34:35.385
So. someone went to all
the trouble of digging a tunnel.

839
00:34:35.387 --> 00:34:37.387
exposing a transatlantic
Internet cable

840
00:34:37.389 --> 00:34:40.323
and murdering a guy all so they
could attach a devise that...

841
00:34:40.325 --> 00:34:42.526
Does absolutely nothing.

842
00:34:56.491 --> 00:34:58.958
I just got off
the phone with Marcus.

843
00:34:58.960 --> 00:35:01.661
So far. Nadim Al-Haj has done a
pretty good job of disappearing.

844
00:35:01.663 --> 00:35:03.129
He's gone to ground.

845
00:35:03.131 --> 00:35:04.363
Knowing now he's
not a hardened terrorist.

846
00:35:04.365 --> 00:35:05.465
I imagine he's quite afraid.

847
00:35:05.467 --> 00:35:07.200
A murder and a flight
from the law

848
00:35:07.202 --> 00:35:08.801
were not part of his plan.

849
00:35:08.803 --> 00:35:10.570
Mason?

850
00:35:10.572 --> 00:35:12.038
Hey.

851
00:35:12.040 --> 00:35:14.173
I thought you were grounded.

852
00:35:14.175 --> 00:35:15.541
From the Internet.

853
00:35:15.543 --> 00:35:18.044
I mean. does this look
like the Internet to you?

854
00:35:18.046 --> 00:35:20.813
So. where New York's
finest nerds failed.

855
00:35:20.815 --> 00:35:23.049
you're hoping
yours will succeed?

856
00:35:23.051 --> 00:35:24.317
No offense to TARU.

857
00:35:24.319 --> 00:35:25.651
But the simple fact is

858
00:35:25.653 --> 00:35:26.919
they must've missed something.

859
00:35:26.921 --> 00:35:28.521
Nadim Al-Haj did not dig

860
00:35:28.523 --> 00:35:30.990
a 50-foot tunnel in order
to install a plastic bauble

861
00:35:30.992 --> 00:35:33.392
with as much function
as a Christmas light.

862
00:35:33.394 --> 00:35:35.328
Until we find out
what the devise does.

863
00:35:35.330 --> 00:35:37.430
we cannot connect
Collin Eisley to any crime.

864
00:35:37.432 --> 00:35:39.866
So. I've solicited
a second opinion.

865
00:35:39.868 --> 00:35:42.435
It's my hope that Mason
will find something

866
00:35:42.437 --> 00:35:43.736
that the police
technicians missed.

867
00:35:43.738 --> 00:35:44.971
I'm trying.

868
00:35:44.973 --> 00:35:46.639
But don't hold you breath.

869
00:35:46.641 --> 00:35:47.874
I'm running parity bit tests.

870
00:35:47.876 --> 00:35:49.709
file compares.
metadata compares.

871
00:35:49.711 --> 00:35:51.611
different character sets.
packet sizes...

872
00:35:51.613 --> 00:35:54.013
You're running tests.

873
00:35:54.015 --> 00:35:55.915
We get it.

874
00:35:58.219 --> 00:36:01.788
I'm gonna get
something to eat.

875
00:36:06.094 --> 00:36:08.995
Upstairs. may I presume
that was Hannah

876
00:36:08.997 --> 00:36:10.663
that you sent to voicemail?

877
00:36:10.665 --> 00:36:12.799
Yeah. I didn't think she
was gonna leave a message.

878
00:36:12.801 --> 00:36:14.534
but she did.

879
00:36:14.536 --> 00:36:16.702
She said she didn't feel great
about how we left things.

880
00:36:16.704 --> 00:36:18.237
and wanted to thank me again.

881
00:36:18.239 --> 00:36:19.939
I mean. she didn't really
come out and say it.

882
00:36:19.941 --> 00:36:22.675
but I got the sense that what
she really wanted to know is

883
00:36:22.677 --> 00:36:24.577
what I'm gonna tell the captain.

884
00:36:24.579 --> 00:36:26.112
What are you gonna tell him?

885
00:36:26.114 --> 00:36:29.015
I don't know. I mean...

886
00:36:29.017 --> 00:36:31.717
he's gonna want to know
what happened. right?

887
00:36:31.719 --> 00:36:35.388
She's a police officer.
but she's also his daughter.

888
00:36:35.390 --> 00:36:37.657
Obviously the truth
will disappoint.

889
00:36:39.961 --> 00:36:42.528
I should tell him.

890
00:36:42.530 --> 00:36:44.730
You should not.

891
00:36:44.732 --> 00:36:46.799
You've expended enough time
and effort on Hannah Gregson.

892
00:36:46.801 --> 00:36:48.568
Telling him will
only embroil you further

893
00:36:48.570 --> 00:36:50.436
and benefit no one.

894
00:36:52.507 --> 00:36:54.307
Well. thanks for not
actually saying the words

895
00:36:54.309 --> 00:36:56.409
“I told you so.”

896
00:36:56.411 --> 00:36:58.444
Well. for the record. I thought
she was a subpar investigator.

897
00:36:58.446 --> 00:37:01.147
I'd no idea she was so cunning.

898
00:37:01.149 --> 00:37:04.317
Anyway. I sent Mason
home for the night.

899
00:37:04.319 --> 00:37:07.587
Thus far. his tests uphold
the dignity of the NYPD.

900
00:37:07.589 --> 00:37:11.123
The stream of zeroes and ones
generated by his tests

901
00:37:11.125 --> 00:37:13.459
entered one end of the device

902
00:37:13.461 --> 00:37:15.828
and emerged a consistent formula
seconds later.

903
00:37:15.830 --> 00:37:17.797
unchanged.

904
00:37:17.799 --> 00:37:19.398
It is quite literally

905
00:37:19.400 --> 00:37:22.001
a box that does nothing.

906
00:37:25.874 --> 00:37:28.674
Unless that's the whole point.

907
00:37:28.676 --> 00:37:29.676
What?

908
00:37:29.677 --> 00:37:30.710
The four milliseconds

909
00:37:30.712 --> 00:37:33.312
that doing nothing would take.

910
00:37:39.988 --> 00:37:41.621
What difference would four
milliseconds make to anything?

911
00:37:41.623 --> 00:37:43.990
In your world and
mine. none at all.

912
00:37:43.992 --> 00:37:46.292
To a human being. it's a
imperceptible amount of time.

913
00:37:46.294 --> 00:37:48.394
But the lion's share of
trading on Wall Street

914
00:37:48.396 --> 00:37:50.663
happens automatically.
via computers.

915
00:37:50.665 --> 00:37:52.331
And in their world.

916
00:37:52.333 --> 00:37:53.699
milliseconds translate

917
00:37:53.701 --> 00:37:56.302
to millions of dollars.

918
00:37:56.304 --> 00:37:58.337
Ruby is the fastest
transatlantic cable

919
00:37:58.339 --> 00:37:59.839
that there is.

920
00:37:59.841 --> 00:38:02.508
Terminates on American
soil at 60 Hudson Street.

921
00:38:02.510 --> 00:38:05.278
where. in order to extract
financial data first.

922
00:38:05.280 --> 00:38:08.848
the top investment firms pay a
premium to house their servers.

923
00:38:08.850 --> 00:38:10.516
Now. any company which
does not lease a space

924
00:38:10.518 --> 00:38:13.286
at 60 Hudson is at
instant disadvantage.

925
00:38:13.288 --> 00:38:17.023
Would you care to guess
which firm is not flush

926
00:38:17.025 --> 00:38:20.593
with enough capital to
earn a spot at 60 Hudson?

927
00:38:22.664 --> 00:38:25.398
Robiskie Investments.

928
00:38:25.400 --> 00:38:27.099
They manage your blind trust.

929
00:38:27.101 --> 00:38:29.502
Only their servers are
in a different building.

930
00:38:29.504 --> 00:38:32.338
Their data comes in from a
slower transatlantic cable.

931
00:38:32.340 --> 00:38:34.874
One that is usually
two milliseconds behind.

932
00:38:34.876 --> 00:38:36.909
A market closes
halfway around the world.

933
00:38:36.911 --> 00:38:38.577
currency drops.
a regime falls--

934
00:38:38.579 --> 00:38:41.547
the news hurdles across
the globe at the speed of light.

935
00:38:41.549 --> 00:38:43.716
The larger firms'
computers buy and sell

936
00:38:43.718 --> 00:38:46.018
thousands of shares before
the one that holds your money

937
00:38:46.020 --> 00:38:47.720
even gets the news.

938
00:38:47.722 --> 00:38:49.555
So you planned
to turn the tables.

939
00:38:49.557 --> 00:38:52.158
Slow Ruby down
by four milliseconds.

940
00:38:52.160 --> 00:38:54.760
Suddenly the big firms are
the ones at a disadvantage.

941
00:38:54.762 --> 00:38:57.463
Your blind trust would
start making more money.

942
00:38:57.465 --> 00:38:58.864
And your hands would stay clean.

943
00:38:58.866 --> 00:39:00.833
Other firms and clients

944
00:39:00.835 --> 00:39:02.868
would benefit. too--
anyone who pulled their data

945
00:39:02.870 --> 00:39:04.770
from a source other than Ruby.

946
00:39:04.772 --> 00:39:06.806
But for a man pathologically
driven to play the game.

947
00:39:06.808 --> 00:39:08.808
that's a small price to pay.

948
00:39:08.810 --> 00:39:11.110
Might even be a plus.

949
00:39:11.112 --> 00:39:14.146
Given that it would hide
your gains amongst the crowd.

950
00:39:15.316 --> 00:39:17.917
You give me a lot of credit.

951
00:39:17.919 --> 00:39:20.152
Like I said before--
it's a brilliant plan.

952
00:39:20.154 --> 00:39:22.421
But... even if you're right.

953
00:39:22.423 --> 00:39:24.457
you still have a problem.

954
00:39:24.459 --> 00:39:26.993
You can't link me to any of it.

955
00:39:26.995 --> 00:39:29.428
Well. when my colleagues and I

956
00:39:29.430 --> 00:39:32.131
got together this morning.
I said the same thing.

957
00:39:32.133 --> 00:39:35.001
I also asked about something
that's been bugging me.

958
00:39:35.003 --> 00:39:37.169
When you first
hired Nadim Al-Haj.

959
00:39:37.171 --> 00:39:39.438
the job didn't include murder.

960
00:39:39.440 --> 00:39:42.575
Once he killed Garrison Boyd.
you must've promised him

961
00:39:42.577 --> 00:39:44.410
a pretty big payday
to keep him quiet.

962
00:39:44.412 --> 00:39:47.213
Especially with him going on
the run for who knows how long.

963
00:39:47.215 --> 00:39:50.149
But with your finances
watched so closely.

964
00:39:50.151 --> 00:39:51.917
how could you pay him?

965
00:39:51.919 --> 00:39:54.687
When I crossed paths
with Mr. Al-Haj the other day.

966
00:39:54.689 --> 00:39:56.355
<i>he absconded</i>
<i>with a poster tube--</i>

967
00:39:56.357 --> 00:39:57.757
a conspicuous detail in itself.

968
00:39:57.759 --> 00:39:59.458
given that he was so busy

969
00:39:59.460 --> 00:40:01.694
destroying so much
other evidence.

970
00:40:01.696 --> 00:40:04.063
I thought perhaps
he'd retained a keepsake--

971
00:40:04.065 --> 00:40:05.364
some schematics.

972
00:40:05.366 --> 00:40:06.799
some leverage to hold over you

973
00:40:06.801 --> 00:40:08.134
should the need arise.

974
00:40:08.136 --> 00:40:09.969
But when Detective Bell
raised his question.

975
00:40:09.971 --> 00:40:13.205
I remembered noticing something
when we were here yesterday.

976
00:40:14.809 --> 00:40:16.642
That's not the same painting
that was here

977
00:40:16.644 --> 00:40:18.844
the first time we visited.

978
00:40:18.846 --> 00:40:20.179
<i>It was a Picasso.</i>

979
00:40:20.181 --> 00:40:21.714
<i>Woman's Portrait.</i>

980
00:40:21.716 --> 00:40:22.948
Not well-known. but

981
00:40:22.950 --> 00:40:25.251
even a lesser work
by the master

982
00:40:25.253 --> 00:40:27.686
must be worth millions.

983
00:40:27.688 --> 00:40:29.321
Is it here?

984
00:40:29.323 --> 00:40:31.323
We've already
reported it stolen.

985
00:40:31.325 --> 00:40:32.725
No dealer is gonna touch it.

986
00:40:32.727 --> 00:40:36.429
Al-Haj won't be able
to get a dime.

987
00:40:36.431 --> 00:40:39.999
You tell us if we're wrong.
Mr. Eisley.

988
00:40:40.001 --> 00:40:42.468
But we don't get the sense
he's a professional killer.

989
00:40:42.470 --> 00:40:44.603
It's only a matter of time
before we find him.

990
00:40:44.605 --> 00:40:46.439
And given that
his payday's going away.

991
00:40:46.441 --> 00:40:49.842
it's a good bet that when we do.
he'll talk.

992
00:40:51.345 --> 00:40:53.179
Now. you like to
make deals. right?

993
00:40:53.181 --> 00:40:55.281
How about
before we find him.

994
00:40:55.283 --> 00:40:57.583
you make one right now?

995
00:41:01.189 --> 00:41:04.557
Oh. Joan?

996
00:41:04.559 --> 00:41:05.624
Hi.

997
00:41:05.626 --> 00:41:07.193
Nice work today.

998
00:41:07.195 --> 00:41:08.894
On the Eisley thing.

999
00:41:08.896 --> 00:41:10.162
Oh. thanks.
Hmm.

1000
00:41:10.164 --> 00:41:11.697
I'll pass that on to Sherlock.

1001
00:41:11.699 --> 00:41:14.467
I'm sorry.

1002
00:41:15.770 --> 00:41:17.403
For what?

1003
00:41:25.346 --> 00:41:27.246
She told you?

1004
00:41:27.248 --> 00:41:29.949
You just seemed a little off
these last couple of days.

1005
00:41:29.951 --> 00:41:32.751
I know it wasn't the credit.

1006
00:41:32.753 --> 00:41:36.655
You and Holmes don't
care about that stuff. but...

1007
00:41:36.657 --> 00:41:38.958
whatever it was...

1008
00:41:38.960 --> 00:41:40.192
You know what?
She just got excited.

1009
00:41:40.194 --> 00:41:41.527
That's all.

1010
00:41:41.529 --> 00:41:44.830
I don't think
you should help her again.

1011
00:41:46.167 --> 00:41:48.501
She is what she is.

1012
00:41:48.503 --> 00:41:50.769
She wants what she wants.

1013
00:41:50.771 --> 00:41:52.838
I love her...

1014
00:41:52.840 --> 00:41:54.840
but I love this job. too.

1015
00:41:54.842 --> 00:41:56.609
